flation input if supply headlines reprice.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eFed Chair Warsh Watch\u003c/div\u003e\u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eForward-Looking Paradigm:\u003c/strong\u003e The draft says desks are looking past regional governor higher-for-longer noise and toward a productivity-led policy baseline.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAI Capex Counterweight:\u003c/strong\u003e The AI infrastructure cycle remains framed as a structural productivity shock and disinflationary shield. Keep it as narrative context, with actual confirmation coming through rates, credit, and earnings breadth.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128200; Trading Strategy Note (ES Futures)\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Breakout Matrix Baseline:\u003c/strong\u003e The May 1 expansion candle remains the structural anchor. Compressed bond volatility and stable funding keep the path of least resistance upward while the liquidity stack holds.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \